{
  "text": "Total nucleic acids were first extracted from microcosm communities [CITATION_1] . Briefly, the samples were resuspended in 500 ml of lysis buffer containing 0.5% sodium dodecyl sulfate, 20 mg ml -1 proteinase K, 20 mg ml -1 of a mixture of lysing enzymes (Sigma, Gillingham, UK). The samples were left to stand at room temperature for 60 min, followed by incubation at 55 1C for 30 min. A solution containing 80 ml of 10% cetyl trimethylammonium bromide solution and 100 ml of 5 M NaCl was added and incubation continued at 65 1C for 10 min. Nucleic acids were extracted with 24:1 isoamyl alcohol:chloroform and precipitated with isopropanol. DNA pellets were cleaned with glacial ethanol, and suspended in 50 ml sterile deionized water. Bacteria-specific primers were used to amplify a roughly 500 bp locus. Each PCR reaction contained 25 pm D4 labelled primer 63f (5 0 -CAGGCCTAACACATGCAAGTC-3 0 ) [CITATION_2] and unlabelled 519r (5 0 -GTATTACCGCGGCTGCTG-3 0 ) [CITATION_3] , 0.2 mM deoxynucleotide triphosphate (dNTPs), 1.25 U Taq DNA polymerase, 5 mg bovine serum albumin and 5 ml of 10 \u00c2 PCR buffer in 50 ml volumes. PCR amplification consisted of an initial denaturing step at 94 1C for 1 min 30 s; 29 cycles of 94 1C for 45 s, 55 1C for 1 min and 72 1C for 1 min 30 s; final extension of 72 1C for 5 min. Millipore (Watford, UK) multiscreen filter plates were used to remove excess PCR reagents, and the remaining nucleic acids were resuspended in 25 ml deionized water. The nucleic acids were subjected to digestion in a 10 ml total reaction volume containing 10 U msp1 enzyme, 1 ml of 10 \u00c2 enzyme buffer, 1 mg bovine serum albumin and approximately 50 ng PCR product. The reaction was incubated for 2 h at 37 1C and tRFLP profiles were analyzed on a Beckman CEQ2000 (Beckman coulter UK Ltd, Gillingham, UK) capillary sequencer. This produced a data matrix consisting of the relative abundances of detected peak sizes (species or operational taxonomic units) contained in each community. Peaks were assigned manually using GeneMarker 1.6 (SoftGenetics, State College, PA, USA) using the settings described by the company [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "83003293",
    "[CITATION_2]": "36004011",
